NT.md` that outlines the experiment design.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0) while only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI≥0.7). This creates a clear hypothesis: CFI-weighted compression should outperform frequency-only compression for predicting next-pulse content.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nDesign the CFI-weighted compression experiment that will test whether filtering by CFI scores improves next-pulse prediction quality over the frequency baseline. Create an experiment specification with methodology, metrics, and implementation approach.\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:28:33\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774362583544}}
